---
import ToolLayout from '../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "What is a Call to Action (CTA)?",
    answer: "A Call to Action (CTA) is a prompt, button, or link on a webpage or post that instructs the viewer to perform a specific action, such as 'Download Ebook' or 'Sign Up Free'."
  },
  {
    question: "How long should a CTA button be?",
    answer: "For maximum conversion, keep button text under 2 to 5 words, or under 20-30 characters. Short, punchy, action-oriented phrases are much easier for users to process."
  },
  {
    question: "Should I write CTA copy in first-person or second-person?",
    answer: "Studies show that first-person CTAs (e.g., 'Start My Free Trial') can increase click-through rates by up to 90% compared to second-person CTAs ('Start Your Free Trial'). Our generator offers templates in both styles."
  },
  {
    question: "What are psychological triggers in CTA design?",
    answer: "Psychological triggers are framing methods that encourage actions, such as Urgency (e.g., 'Offer Ends Today'), Benefit-driven ('Boost My Traffic'), or Low-risk ('No Credit Card Required')."
  },
  {
    question: "How do I choose the right color for my CTA button?",
    answer: "Use a color that highly contrasts with your website's background. Color psychology is less important than visual hierarchy—the button must stand out immediately."
  }
];
---

<ToolLayout
  title="CTA Generator - Free Call to Action Maker"
  description="Generate high-converting CTA copy for landing pages, ads, and social media. Free online button and link call to action generator."
  toolName="CTA Generator"
  toolDescription="Generate high-performing CTA button copy, anchor links, and social media hooks. Customize your goal and trigger to write copy that converts."
  category="Writing Tools"
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <div slot="calculator" class="calc-card glass">
    <!-- Main Advanced Grid Layout -->
    <div class="calc-grid">
      <!-- Left Column: Settings and Input Forms -->
      <div class="calc-form-column">
        <form class="calc-form" id="generator-form" onsubmit="return false;">
          <!-- Offer Goal -->
          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="value-input" class="icon-label">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="field-icon">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M16.862 4.487 1.687-1.688a1.875 1.875 0 1 1 2.652 2.652L10.582 16.07a4.5 4.5 0 0 1-1.897 1.13L6 18l.8-2.685a4.5 4.5 0 0 1 1.13-1.897l8.932-8.931Zm0 0L19.5 7.125M18 14v4.75A2.25 2.25 0 0 1 15.75 21H5.25A2.25 2.25 0 0 1 3 18.75V8.25A2.25 2.25 0 0 1 5.25 6H10" />
              </svg>
              What is the goal of your offer? (Action)
            </label>
            <input type="text" id="value-input" class="form-input" placeholder="e.g. download ebook, join newsletter, start free trial" value="download my free guide" required />
          </div>

          <!-- CTA Format Type -->
          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="format-input" class="icon-label">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="field-icon">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 17.25v1.007a3 3 0 0 1-.879 2.122L7.5 21h9l-.621-.621A3 3 0 0 1 15 18.257V17.25m6-12V15a2.25 2.25 0 0 1-2.25 2.25H5.25A2.25 2.25 0 0 1 3 15V5.25A2.25 2.25 0 0 1 5.25 3h13.5A2.25 2.25 0 0 1 21 5.25Z" />
              </svg>
              CTA Format / Type
            </label>
            <select id="format-input" class="form-input" style="height: 48px; border-radius: 8px;">
              <option value="Button" selected>Button Text (Short & Punchy)</option>
              <option value="Anchor">Anchor Link (Benefit-driven)</option>
              <option value="Social">Social Hook (Attention grabber)</option>
            </select>
          </div>

          <!-- Psychological Trigger -->
          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="trigger-input" class="icon-label">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="field-icon">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15.042 9.152c.582.448 1.148.89 1.676 1.345m-1.676-1.345c-.53-.407-1.09-.785-1.676-1.133m3.352 2.478c.53.407 1.09.785 1.676 1.133M15.042 9.152c-.582-.448-1.148-.89-1.676-1.345M12 21a9.003 9.003 0 0 0 8.354-5.646 9.003 9.003 0 0 0-16.708 0A9.003 9.003 0 0 0 12 21Z" />
              </svg>
              Psychological Trigger
            </label>
            <select id="trigger-input" class="form-input" style="height: 48px; border-radius: 8px;">
              <option value="Benefit" selected>Benefit-driven (Value focus)</option>
              <option value="Urgency">Urgency / Scarcity (Time focus)</option>
              <option value="Risk">Low Risk (Safety focus)</option>
              <option value="Curiosity">Curiosity (Discovery focus)</option>
            </select>
          </div>

          <!-- Tone Selection -->
          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="tone-input" class="icon-label">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="field-icon">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15.182 15.182a4.5 4.5 0 0 1-6.364 0M21 12a9 9 0 1 1-18 0 9 9 0 0 1 18 0ZM9.75 9.75c0 .414-.168.75-.375.75S9 10.164 9 9.75 9.168 9 9.375 9s.375.336.375.75Zm-.375 0h.008v.015h-.008V9.75Zm5.625 0c0 .414-.168.75-.375.75s-.375-.336-.375-.75.168-.75.375-.75.375.336.375.75Zm-.375 0h.008v.015h-.008V9.75Z" />
              </svg>
              Select Tone Style
            </label>
            <select id="tone-input" class="form-input" style="height: 48px; border-radius: 8px;">
              <option value="Action" selected>Action-oriented & Direct</option>
              <option value="Friendly">Friendly & Supportive</option>
              <option value="Bold">Direct & Bold</option>
            </select>
          </div>

          <div class="form-actions">
            <button type="button" id="generate-btn" class="calc-btn" style="width: 100%;">Generate CTA</button>
            <button type="button" id="calc-reset-btn" class="calc-btn-secondary" style="width: 100%;">Reset Fields</button>
          </div>
        </form>
      </div>

      <!-- Right Column: Interactive Sandbox Editor & Landing Mockup -->
      <div class="calc-editor-column">
        <!-- Live Landing Page CTA Mockup -->
        <div class="landing-mockup glass" style="border: 1.5px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 20px; padding: 1.5rem; text-align: center; background: var(--color-bg-alt); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; align-items: center; justify-content: center; min-height: 200px;">
          <span style="font-size: 0.65rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-text-muted); text-transform: uppercase; border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--color-border); padding-bottom: 0.25rem; display: block; width: 100%; text-align: left;">Live Button Mockup Preview</span>
          
          <h4 style="margin: 0.25rem 0 0 0; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-text);">Get the Ultimate Creator Guide</h4>
          <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.4; max-width: 280px;">
            Learn how to write optimized copy, track character thresholds, and grow your audience.
          </p>

          <!-- Interactive styled button preview -->
          <button type="button" id="mockup-cta-btn" class="calc-btn" style="margin-top: 0.5rem; width: auto; min-width: 180px; padding: 0 1.75rem; box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.25); font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 700; transition: all var(--transition-normal);">
            Get My Free Guide
          </button>
          
          <span style="font-size: 0.68rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.15rem;" id="mockup-subtext">No email signup required. Instantly download.</span>
        </div>

        <!-- Sandbox Active Workspace Editor -->
        <div class="sandbox-box glass">
          <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
            <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-text); text-transform: uppercase;">Active CTA Sandbox</span>
            <span id="sandbox-counter" style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-text-muted);">18 / 30 Chars</span>
          </div>
          
          <textarea id="sandbox-input" class="form-input" style="height: 60px; resize: none; line-height: 1.4; font-size: 0.95rem; font-family: inherit; padding-top: 0.5rem;" placeholder="Refine your CTA text manually here..."></textarea>

          <!-- Visual character budget progress bar -->
          <div class="progress-bar-container" style="background: var(--color-border); height: 6px; border-radius: 4px; overflow: hidden; margin: 0.5rem 0;">
            <div id="progress-bar-fill" style="width: 60%; height: 100%; background: var(--color-brand); transition: all var(--transition-fast);"></div>
          </div>

          <!-- Quick Emoji Panel -->
          <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.25rem; margin-top: 0.5rem;">
            <span style="font-size: 0.65rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-text-muted); text-transform: uppercase;">Quick Insert Emojis:</span>
            <div class="emoji-selector-panel" id="emoji-picker-container">
              <button type="button" class="emoji-btn">👇</button>
              <button type="button" class="emoji-btn">📈</button>
              <button type="button" class="emoji-btn">🚀</button>
              <button type="button" class="emoji-btn">🔥</button>
              <button type="button" class="emoji-btn">📥</button>
              <button type="button" class="emoji-btn">🎁</button>
              <button type="button" class="emoji-btn">💡</button>
              <button type="button" class="emoji-btn">⚡</button>
              <button type="button" class="emoji-btn">✨</button>
              <button type="button" class="emoji-btn">➡️</button>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; margin-top: 1rem;">
            <button type="button" id="copy-active-btn" class="calc-btn" style="flex: 1.2; height: 42px; font-size: 0.85rem;">Copy CTA Copy</button>
            <button type="button" id="clear-sandbox-btn" class="calc-btn-secondary" style="flex: 0.8; height: 42px; font-size: 0.85rem;">Clear</button>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Suggestions Drawer Panel -->
        <div class="suggestions-drawer" id="suggestions-box" style="margin-top: 1.5rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem;">
          <h4 style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-text); text-transform: uppercase; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); padding-bottom: 0.5rem;">Alternative CTA Variations</h4>
          
          <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem;">
            <!-- Card Option A -->
            <div class="option-card">
              <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">
                <span class="opt-label">Option A (Direct Action)</span>
                <span id="opt-1-badge" class="opt-badge">0 / 30</span>
              </div>
              <p id="opt-1-val" class="opt-text">Get My Free Guide</p>
              <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; margin-top: 0.5rem;">
                <button type="button" class="load-sandbox-btn mock-btn-mini" data-target="opt-1-val">Load to Sandbox</button>
                <button type="button" class="copy-direct-btn mock-btn-mini secondary" data-target="opt-1-val">Copy</button>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Card Option B -->
            <div class="option-card">
              <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">
                <span class="opt-label">Option B (Benefit focus)</span>
                <span id="opt-2-badge" class="opt-badge">0 / 30</span>
              </div>
              <p id="opt-2-val" class="opt-text">Download & Grow My Reach</p>
              <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; margin-top: 0.5rem;">
                <button type="button" class="load-sandbox-btn mock-btn-mini" data-target="opt-2-val">Load to Sandbox</button>
                <button type="button" class="copy-direct-btn mock-btn-mini secondary" data-target="opt-2-val">Copy</button>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Card Option C -->
            <div class="option-card">
              <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">
                <span class="opt-label">Option C (Low Risk)</span>
                <span id="opt-3-badge" class="opt-badge">0 / 30</span>
              </div>
              <p id="opt-3-val" class="opt-text">Get Free Guide Instantly</p>
              <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; margin-top: 0.5rem;">
                <button type="button" class="load-sandbox-btn mock-btn-mini" data-target="opt-3-val">Load to Sandbox</button>
                <button type="button" class="copy-direct-btn mock-btn-mini secondary" data-target="opt-3-val">Copy</button>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div slot="about" class="editorial-content">
    <h2>CTA Generator: Write High-Converting Call to Action Button Copy</h2>
    <div style="margin: 1.5rem 0; background: var(--color-bg-alt); padding: 1.25rem; border-radius: var(--radius-md); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-brand);">
      <p style="margin: 0; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        📈 <strong>Looking to optimize your landing page conversion rates?</strong> Read our comprehensive strategy guide on <a href="/blog/cta-generator-guide" style="color: var(--color-brand); text-decoration: underline;">CTA Optimization & Conversion Copywriting</a> to learn how to choose strong verbs, position buttons, and run A/B testing checks.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3>Introduction</h3>
    <p>
      The final link in your marketing funnel is the Call to Action. Even if your landing page has great copy, a weak or confusing button (like a generic 'Submit') can lose potential conversions. This free <strong>cta generator</strong> or <strong>call to action generator</strong> helps you quickly generate action-oriented button texts, benefit-focused links, and eye-catching social hooks.
    </p>

    <h3>How to Use This Tool</h3>
    <p>
      To write high-converting CTAs, follow these instructions:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Define Offer:</strong> Input your product offer or campaign goal in the top text field.</li>
      <li><strong>Select Format:</strong> Choose whether you need Button Text, Anchor Link copy, or a Social Hook.</li>
      <li><strong>Select Trigger:</strong> Select a Benefit-driven, Urgency, Curiosity, or Low-Risk psychological trigger.</li>
      <li><strong>Select Tone:</strong> Select Action-oriented, Friendly, or Bold.</li>
      <li><strong>Generate & Edit:</strong> Click <strong>Generate CTA</strong>, select an option to load into the Sandbox, edit, and copy.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>What is CTA?</h3>
    <p>
      A <strong>CTA</strong> (Call to Action) is a marketing term for any prompt that tells the reader what to do next. It is usually designed as a clickable button (e.g. "Buy Now"), a text hyperlink (e.g. "Read the full study"), or a direct hook at the end of a video or social post (e.g. "Comment below for the link").
    </p>

    <h3>How Does a Good CTA Help Generate More Leads?</h3>
    <p>
      A well-optimized CTA plays a crucial role in converting visitors into leads:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Reduces Friction:</strong> Direct, clear buttons show the user exactly what they will get (e.g., "Download Free PDF" is much clearer than "Submit").</li>
      <li><strong>Sets Clear Expectations:</strong> Action verbs clarify what the click will do, reducing uncertainty.</li>
      <li><strong>Creates Urgency:</strong> Time-sensitive phrasing encourages visitors to act immediately rather than leaving.</li>
      <li><strong>Highlights the Value:</strong> Benefit-driven styling answers the visitor's core question: "What is in this for me?".</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>How Does It Work?</h3>
    <p>
      The generator constructs copy using structured copywriting formulas:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Action Verb Hook:</strong> Injects strong action words (e.g., Get, Claim, Download, Start, Join).</li>
      <li><strong>First-Person Framing:</strong> Uses terms like "My" or "Me" (e.g., "Start My Trial"), which increases click rates.</li>
      <li><strong>Low-Risk Modifiers:</strong> Appends safety phrases (e.g., "Free", "No Card Required", "Cancel Anytime") to reduce barrier hesitation.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Example Calculation</h3>
    <p>
      Let's look at how the tool structures a button CTA:
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Selected Parameters:</strong><br />
      ✦ Offer Goal: "download my free guide"<br />
      ✦ Trigger: "Benefit-driven"<br />
      ✦ Format: "Button Text"
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Formatting Process:</strong><br />
      ✦ Step 1: Extract action noun $\rightarrow$ "free guide"<br />
      ✦ Step 2: Inject action verb $\rightarrow$ "Get My Free Guide"<br />
      ✦ Step 3: Check character length $\rightarrow$ <strong>18 characters</strong>.<br />
      ✦ Budget Check: The length is under the 25-character recommended button limit, ensuring the text fits perfectly inside landing page buttons on mobile devices.
    </p>

    <h3>Who Should Use This Tool?</h3>
    <p>
      This <strong>free call to action generator</strong> is designed for:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Copywriters & Marketers:</strong> Writing ad copy and landing page headers.</li>
      <li><strong>SEO Consultants:</strong> Creating high-converting anchor text links.</li>
      <li><strong>SaaS Creators:</strong> Designing buttons for signup pages.</li>
      <li><strong>Social Media Managers:</strong> Writing hooks to drive link clicks in bios.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>

<style>
